      <div class="lg-faq-list">
        <details class="lg-faq-item">
          <summary class="lg-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you still repair LG phones in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="lg-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="lg-faq-answer">Yes — we're one of the few repair shops in Winnipeg still specialising in LG devices after the brand exited the smartphone market in 2021. We maintained our supplier relationships specifically to keep supporting LG owners who don't want to be forced into a replacement.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="lg-faq-item">
          <summary class="lg-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you still get LG phone parts in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="lg-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="lg-faq-answer">Yes — we maintain active supplier relationships for LG Velvet, V series, G series, Stylo, and K series parts. Popular models are often in stock for same-day repairs, while rarer models like the LG Wing may require a short sourcing window — contact us to confirm availability for your specific model.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="lg-faq-item">
          <summary class="lg-faq-summary">
            <span>How long does LG screen repair take in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="lg-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
